line_1: Where on the surface Lead, like feathers, swims;
line_2: There let me bathe my yet unhallow'd limbs,

line_1: Of those that fly, while he that swims
And instant, lo, his dizzy eye-ball swims
line_2: Pain with strong grasp distorts his writhing limbs,

line_1: Surround the timorous Beauty, as she swims,
line_2: And gaze enamour'd on her silver limbs.

line_1: Wave over wave the driving desert swims,
line_2: Bursts o'er their heads, inhumes their struggling limbs;

line_1: Through gaping seams the rushing deluge swims,
line_2: Chills their pale bosoms, bathes their shuddering limbs,

line_1: And Frost and Famine follow as he swims. —
line_2: Spreads o'er the shuddering Line his shadowy limbs,

line_1: High on the flood with speckled bosom swims,
line_2: Helm'd with broad tail, and oar'd with giant limbs;

line_1: O'er her warm cheek the blush of beauty swims,
line_2: And nerves Herculean bend her sinewy limbs;

line_1: Pleased on the boiling wave old AESON swims,
line_2: And feels new vigour stretch his swelling limbs;

line_1: Loose o'er the flood her azure mantle swims,
line_2: And the clear stream betrays her snowy limbs.

line_1: The head in wild distraction swims;
line_2: Cold sweats bedew the trembling limbs;
